{"lemma":"عَن","slug":"عَن","root":"ع.ن","root_slug":"ع-ن","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ن","pos":"PREP","pos_camel":"prep","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"عَن","root":"","pos":"P","occurrence_count":465},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","prep","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":18},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n30640","n30649","n30648","n30650","n30840"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8E%D9%86"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"prep","gloss":"off, away from"},{"pos":"prep","gloss":"from (source)"},{"pos":"prep","gloss":"out of (a feeling)"},{"pos":"prep","gloss":"about, on"},{"pos":"prep","gloss":"according to, as attested by, on authority of"},{"pos":"prep","gloss":"on the basis of, on the strength of"},{"pos":"prep","gloss":"for, in defense of"},{"pos":"prep","gloss":"as a substitute for"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to present itself, to offer itself"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to take shape, to form, to arise, to spring up"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to suggest itself"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to appear, to occur"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to turn away, to move aside"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to put a rein on"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to pull the reins on"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to confine, to enclose"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to vilify, to revile"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of عَنَّ (ʕanna) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root ع ن ن (ʕ n n) in the sense of appearing in view in the distance and in the sense offering or presenting, bring it into someone’s view; related to ع ي ن (ʕ y n) a root denoting the eye and vision."},"ipa":["/ʕan/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n30640","headword_ar":"عَنَّ","root":"En","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) the former accord. to some relaters, and the latter accord. to others, occurring in a verse of a Hudhalee, (TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EananN","text_ar":"عَنَنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ean~N","text_ar":"عَنٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EunuwnN","text_ar":"عُنُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the first of which is also [or is properly] a simple subst., (K, [and such, in one sense, it is said to be in the Msb, as will be shown in what follows,]) said of an affair, or event, (Msb,) or of a thing, (S, * K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It appeared before one:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) [and]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaraDa","text_ar":"عَرَضَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh) and (S, K)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiEotaraDa","text_ar":"اِعْتَرَضَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it appeared; it showed, presented,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"offered, itself: it occurred:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it presented itself,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intervened between a person and an object before him, as an obstacle: it opposed itself"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiEotan~a","text_ar":"اِعْتَنَّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, K.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EananN","text_ar":"عَنَنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below.] Imra-el-Keys says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"faEan~a lanaA sirobN kaA^an~a niEaAjahu\n                      \n                     \n                        Ea*aAraY dawaArK fiY mulaA='K mu*ay~ali"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2163},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, TA, *) meaning,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaraDa","text_ar":"عَرَضَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And there appeared to us a herd"},{"kind":"text","text":"of wild oxen,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as though the females thereof were virgins"},{"kind":"text","text":"making the circuit"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of Dawár,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Duwár, in long-skirted garments of the kind called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mulaA='","text_ar":"مُلَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"; Dawár, or Duwár, being the name of an idol around which the people of the Time of Ignorance used to curcuit. (Mgh, * and EM pp. 46 and 47.) And one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA A^afoEaluhu maA Ean~a fiY Als~amaA='i najomN","text_ar":"لَا اَفْعَلُهُ مَا عَنَّ فِى السَّمَا=ءِ نَجْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA EaraDa","text_ar":"مَا عَرَضَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will not do it as long as a star appears in the sky"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ean~a","text_ar":"عَنَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, TA,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EananN","text_ar":"عَنَنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) or this is a simple subst., (Msb, TA,) and the inf. n. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ean~N","text_ar":"عَنٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He opposed himself"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiEotaraDa","text_ar":"اِعْتَرَضَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", Msb, or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEar~aDa","text_ar":"تَعَرَّضَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to another"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from right and left,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from either side of him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with an abominable,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evil, action."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ean~a","text_ar":"عَنَّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eani Al$~aYo'i","text_ar":"عَنِ الشَّىْءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", [inf. n., app.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ean~N","text_ar":"عَنٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He turned aside,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"away, from the thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b4-  Hence the saying of the lawyers,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ean~a Eani A@moraA^apK duwna A^uxoraY","text_ar":"عَنَّ عَنِ ا@مْرَاَةٍ دُونَ اُخْرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He turned away from one woman, not"},{"kind":"text","text":"from"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"another"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he desired not one woman, but desired another:"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus in the active form: and one may also say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eun~a","text_ar":"عُنَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. in the passive form [from one or another of the following significations of the trans. verb]. (Msb.) For the latter of these, and its var."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eunina","text_ar":"عُنِنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", see 2.       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eananotu All~ijaAma","text_ar":"عَنَنْتُ اللِّجَامَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 4. ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ean~a daAb~atahu","text_ar":"عَنَّ دَابَّتَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He put a rein"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EinaAn","text_ar":"عِنَان"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to his beast."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eananotu Alfarasa","text_ar":"عَنَنْتُ الفَرَسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) in the M [↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ean~anotu","text_ar":"عَنَّنْتُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":",] with tesh-deed; (TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I withheld the horse by means of his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EinaAn","text_ar":"عِنَان"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rein"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, Msb, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEonanotuhu","text_ar":"اَعْنَنْتُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfarasa","text_ar":"الفَرَسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEonanotu","text_ar":"اَعْنَنْتُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I put a rein to the horse:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) and it is said in the T that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfaArisu","text_ar":"الفَارِسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEan~a","text_ar":"اَعَنَّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the horseman drew,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pulled, the rein of his beast, to turn him back,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"away, from his course."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eananotuhu","text_ar":"عَنَنْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eun~a","text_ar":"عُنَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I confined him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he was confined,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eun~ap","text_ar":"عُنَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"enclosure"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the camels."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eananotu fulaAnFA","text_ar":"عَنَنْتُ فُلَانًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I reviled such a one; vilified him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gave a bad name to him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)       -A4-  See also Q. Q. 1."}],"source_refs":["S","Mgh","Msb","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n30649","headword_ar":"عَنَّ","root":"En","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^an~a","text_ar":"اَنَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see the next preceding paragraph, last quarter."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n30648","headword_ar":"عَنْ","root":"En","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"is used in three manners:       -A2-  First, it is a prep.: and as such it has ten meanings. (Mughnee, K.) ―         -b2-  (1) It denotes transition; (Msb, Mughnee, K;) either sensibly or virtually; (Msb;) and the Basrees have mentioned no other meaning than this: (Mughnee:) or, as Sb expresses it, (Msb,) it denotes what has passed [or rather it denotes passage] from the thing [that is mentioned immediately after it]: (S, Msb:) Er-Rághib says that it necessarily denotes transition from that to the mention of which it is prefixed: and the grammarians say that it is applied to denote what has passed and become remote from thee. (TA.) Thus in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAfarotu Eani Albaladi","text_ar":"سَافَرْتُ عَنِ البَلَدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I journeyed from the country,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"town"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Mughnee, K. *) And in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ragibotu","text_ar":"رَغِبْتُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eano ka*aA","text_ar":"عَنْ كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I abstained from such a thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and hence,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I did not desire,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wish for, such a thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Mughnee.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramayotu Eani Alqawosi","text_ar":"رَمَيْتُ عَنِ القَوْسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I shot"},{"kind":"text","text":"an arrow, or arrows,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the bow"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, Mughnee;) because by means of the bow one projects his arrow from the bow, and makes it to pass therefrom: (S:) but another meaning of this will be mentioned in what follows. (Mughnee.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aToEamotuhu Eano juwEK","text_ar":"اَطْعَمْتُهُ عَنْ جُوعٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I fed him"},{"kind":"text","text":"so as to free him"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from hunger"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, Msb;) making hunger to be quitted, and passed from: (S, * Msb:) and in this case,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino","text_ar":"مِنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used in its place, (S, TA,) as in the Kur cvi. 3; (TA;) or the meaning in this instance is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"because of hunger."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Jel.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jalasotu","text_ar":"جَلَسْتُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eano yamiynihi","text_ar":"عَنْ يَمِينِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [as though] meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I sat passing away from the place of his right side, in sitting, to another place"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"adjacent thereto:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but see another explanation near the end of the paragraph]. (Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AinoSarifo Ean~iY","text_ar":"اِنْصَرِفْ عَنِّى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tanaH~a Ean~iY","text_ar":"تَنَحَّ عَنِّى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Turn thou,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"go thou, away,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"aside, from me"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axa*otu AlEiloma Eanohu","text_ar":"اَخَذْتُ العِلْمَ عَنْهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I understood,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became acquainted with,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"acquired,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"knowledge,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"science, from him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as though the understanding passed from him. (Msb.) [And similar to this is the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rawaY Eano fulaAnK","text_ar":"رَوَى عَنْ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", for which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eano","text_ar":"عَنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnK","text_ar":"فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"alone (the verb being understood) is often used,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He related"},{"kind":"text","text":"a tradition or traditions &c. as learned, or heard, or received,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from such a one,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on the authority of such a one."},{"kind":"text","text":"In many other phrases also, some of which will be mentioned in treating of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eano","text_ar":"عَنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino","text_ar":"مِنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the former of these two prepositions is to be, or may be, expl. as denoting transition. For ex., one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dafaEa","text_ar":"دَفَعَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eanohu","text_ar":"عَنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAfaEa","text_ar":"دَافَعَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He repelled from him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and hence,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he defended him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dfE","text_ar":"دفع"},{"kind":"text","text":":) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramaY Eanohumo","text_ar":"رَمَى عَنْهُمْ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He shot in defence of them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see an ex. in a verse cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEobuwlN","text_ar":"مَعْبُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eanohu","text_ar":"عَنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is sometimes used for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"difaAEFA Eanohu","text_ar":"دِفَاعًا عَنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAtalotu Eanohu","text_ar":"قَاتَلْتُ عَنْهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I fought in defence of him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"repelling from him."},{"kind":"text","text":"But the instances of this and other usages of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eano","text_ar":"عَنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", exclusive of those mentioned in this paragraph, depending upon verbs or part. ns. expressed or obviously understood, are far too numerous to be here collected: many of these will be found among the explanations of words with which they occur.] ―         -b3-  (2) It denotes a compensation; or something given, or received, or put, or done, instead, or in lieu, of another thing. (Mughnee, K.) Thus in the saying [in the Kur ii. 45],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wa A@t~aquwA yawomFA laA tajoziY nafosN Eano nafosK $ayoy^FA","text_ar":"وَ ا@تَّقُوا يَوْمًا لَا تَجْزِى نَفْسٌ عَنْ نَفْسٍ شَيْيًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And fear"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2164},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ye a day"},{"kind":"text","text":"wherein"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a soul shall not give anything as a satisfaction for a soul,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for another soul:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shall not make satisfaction for a soul at all;"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to the latter rendering,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$yy^A","text_ar":"شييا"},{"kind":"text","text":"being put in the accus. case after the manner of an inf. n.]. (Mughnee, K. *) And in the saying in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuwmiY Eano A^um~iki","text_ar":"صُومِى عَنْ اُمِّكِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fast thou for,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in lieu of, thy mother"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Mughnee.) ―         -b4-  (3) It denotes superiority ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlAisotiEolaA='","text_ar":"الاِسْتِعْلَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as used tropically]); (Mughnee, K;) i. e. as"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY","text_ar":"عَلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mughnee.) Thus in the saying of Dhu-l-Isba' El-'Adwánee,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"laAhi A@bonu Eam~ika laA A^afoDalota fiY HasabK\n                      \n                     \n                        Ean~iY walaA A^anota day~aAniY fataxozuwaniY"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mughnee,) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"To God be attributed the excellence of the son of thy paternal uncle"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the meaning being"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lil~`hi dar~u A@boni Eam~ika","text_ar":"لِلّٰهِ دَرُّ ا@بْنِ عَمِّكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thou hast not become possessed of superiority, in grounds of pretension to respect"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"honour, above me,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"over me,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY~a","text_ar":"عَلَىَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nor art thou my governor that thou shouldst rule me;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for the well-known mode is to say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afoDalotu Ealayohi","text_ar":"اَفْضَلْتُ عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mughnee.) [Thus too in the phrases"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEaZ~ama Eanohu","text_ar":"تَعَظَّمَ عَنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEaAZama Eanohu","text_ar":"تَعَاظَمَ عَنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(expl. in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EZm","text_ar":"عظم"},{"kind":"text","text":"), and in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tajaAl~a Eanohu","text_ar":"تَجَالَّ عَنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(expl. in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jl","text_ar":"جل"},{"kind":"text","text":"), and the like.] And thus it has been said to be used in the phrase [in the Kur xxxviii. 31],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~iY A^aHobabotu Hub~a A@loxayori Eano *ikori rab~iY","text_ar":"اـِنِّى اَحْبَبْتُ حُبَّ ا@لْخَيْرِ عَنْ ذِكْرِ رَبِّى"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qad~amotuhu Ealayohi","text_ar":"قَدَّمْتُهُ عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily I have preferred the love of good things above,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to, the remembrance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"praise, of my Lord"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: but it is also said that it is here used in its proper manner, as dependent upon a denotative of state suppressed; the meaning being,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"munoSarifFA Eano *ikori rab~iY","text_ar":"مُنْصَرِفًا عَنْ ذِكْرِ رَبِّى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"turning away from the remembrance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]: and AO is related to have said that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHobabotu","text_ar":"اَحْبَبْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHab~a","text_ar":"اَحَبَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbaEiyru","text_ar":"البَعِيرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", signifying “ the camel lay down and did not become roused; ” and that the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I have become withheld by the love of good things from the remembrance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. (Mughnee.) And it is [said to be] used as denoting superiority or the like in the saying [in the Kur xlvii. last verse],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faA_in~amaA yaboxalu Eano nfosihi","text_ar":"فَاـِنَّمَا يَبْخَلُ عَنْ نفْسِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as though the meaning were"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is niggardly only to himself"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY nafosihi","text_ar":"عَلَى نَفْسِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY","text_ar":"عَلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is considered in this case as importing an ideal superiority); but the phrase may be better rendered, agreeably with the proper, or primary, signification of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eano","text_ar":"عَنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he withholds, with niggardliness, only from himself;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as is indicated by Bd]. (Mughnee, K.) ―         -b5-  (4) It denotes a cause. (Mughnee, K.) Thus in the saying [in the Kur ix. 115],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wamaA kaAna A@sotigofaAru A_ibor`hiyma liA^abiyhi A_il~aA Eano mawoEidapK","text_ar":"وَمَا كَانَ ا@سْتِغْفَارُ اـِبْرٰهِيمَ لِاَبِيهِ اـِلَّا عَنْ مَوْعِدَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And Abraham's begging forgiveness for his father was not otherwise than because of a promise"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Mughnee, K.) And thus in the saying [in the Kur xi. 56],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wamaA naHonu bitaArikiY A=lihatinaA Eano qawolika","text_ar":"وَمَا نَحْنُ بِتَارِكِى ا=لِهَتِنَا عَنْ قَوْلِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And we are not,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"will not be, relinquishers of our gods because of thy saying"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: or the meaning may be,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"we do not,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"will not, relinquish our gods, turning away"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAdiriyna","text_ar":"صَادِرِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as a denotative of state relating to the pronoun [implied] in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tArkY","text_ar":"تاركى"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from thy saying;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and this is the opinion of Z. (Mughnee.) [See also an ex. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"danodana","text_ar":"دَنْدَنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", last sentence.] ―         -b6-  (5) It is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baEoda","text_ar":"بَعْدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, Mughnee, K.) Thus in the saying [in the Kur xxiii. 42],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eam~aA qaliylK","text_ar":"عَمَّا قَلِيلٍ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layuSobiHun~a naAdimiyna","text_ar":"لَيُصْبِحُنَّ نَادِمِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mughnee, K,) meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baEoda","text_ar":"بَعْدَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaliylK","text_ar":"قَلِيلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"After a little"},{"kind":"text","text":"while,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they will assuredly become repentant"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And in the phrase [in the Kur lxxxiv. 19],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"latarokabun~a TabaqFA Eano TabaqK","text_ar":"لَتَرْكَبُنَّ طَبَقًا عَنْ طَبَقٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[expl. in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tbq","text_ar":"طبق"},{"kind":"text","text":"], meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAlapF baEoda HaAlapK","text_ar":"حَالَةً بَعْدَ حَالَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mughnee.) And in the saying,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"wamanohalK waradotuhu Eano manohalK"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And to many a watering-place have I come after a watering-place"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Mughnee.) And in the saying of El-Hárith Ibn-'Obád,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"qar~ibaA marobaTa Aln~aEaAmapi min~iY\n                      \n                     \n                        laqiHato Harobu wAy^ilK Eano HiyaAli"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * TA,) meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baEoda HiyaAlK","text_ar":"بَعْدَ حِيَالٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Make ye two to be near to me the place of the tying of En-Na'ámeh"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the name of a horse of the poet):"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the war of Wáïl has become pregnant after failing to be pregnant during a year,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"years"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And in the saying of Et-Tirimmáh,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"sayaEolamu kul~uhumo A^an~iY musin~N\n                      \n                     ↓ \n      A_i*aA dafaEuwA EinaAnFA Eano EinaAni"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"All of them shall know that I am of full age, when they press forward"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heat after heat."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b7-  (6) It denotes the meaning of the preposition"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY","text_ar":"فِى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mughnee, K.) Thus in the saying,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"walaA taku Eano Hamoli Alr~ibaAEapi waAniyaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And be not thou remiss in bearing the responsibility of the obligation that thou takest upon thyself"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; as is shown by the phrase, [in the Kur xx. 44],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walaA taniyaA fiY *ikoriY","text_ar":"وَلَا تَنِيَا فِى ذِكْرِى"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mughnee, K:) so it is said; but it seems that the meaning of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wanaY","text_ar":"وَنَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eano ka*aA","text_ar":"عَنْ كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"is, “ he passed from such a thing, not entering upon it; ” and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wanaY fiyhi","text_ar":"وَنَى فِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", “ he entered upon it but was remiss, or languid: ” by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~ibaAEap","text_ar":"الرِّبَاعَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is meant"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the payment of a bloodwit"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mughnee.) ―         -b8-  (7) It is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino","text_ar":"مِنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mughnee, K.) Thus in the saying [in the Kur xlii. 24],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wahuwa","text_ar":"وَهُوَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@l~a*iY yaqobalu A@lt~awobapa Eano EibaAdihi","text_ar":"ا@لَّذِى يَقْبَلُ ا@لتَّوْبَةَ عَنْ عِبَادِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And He is he who accepts repentance from his servants"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (AO, Mughnee, K.) Az mentions among the cases in which there is a difference between"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino","text_ar":"مِنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eano","text_ar":"عَنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", that the former has adjoined to it a noun signifying what is near; and the latter, [one signifying] what is remote; as in one's saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samiEotu mino","text_ar":"سَمِعْتُ مِنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnK HadiyvFA","text_ar":"فُلَانٍ حَدِيثًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I heard from such a one a narrative"},{"kind":"text","text":"], and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Had~avaniY Eano fulaAnK HadiyvFA","text_ar":"حَدَّثَنِى عَنْ فُلَانٍ حَدِيثًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He related to me a narrative from such a one,"},{"kind":"text","text":"a phrase similar to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rawaY Eano fulaAnK","text_ar":"رَوَى عَنْ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", mentioned among exs. of the first meaning of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"En","text_ar":"عن"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: accord. to As, one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Had~avaniY fulaAnN mino fulaAnK","text_ar":"حَدَّثَنِى فُلَانٌ مِنْ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eanohu","text_ar":"عَنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one related to me from such a one"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahiytu mino","text_ar":"لَهِيتُ مِنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnK","text_ar":"فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eanohu","text_ar":"عَنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I became diverted from such a one so as to forget him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: accord. to Ks, one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahiytu Eanohu","text_ar":"لَهِيتُ عَنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"only: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eanoka jaA='a h`*aA","text_ar":"عَنْكَ جَا=ءَ هٰذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"minoka","text_ar":"مِنْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"From thee came this"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b9-  (8) It is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bi","text_ar":"بِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mughnee, K.) Thus [it is said to be used] in the phrase [in the Kur liii. 3],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wamaA yanoTiqu Eani A@lohawaY","text_ar":"وَمَا يَنْطِقُ عَنِ ا@لْهَوَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Nor does he speak with the desire of self-gratification"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Mughnee, K:) but it seems that it is here used in its proper [or primary] sense; and that the meaning is,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wamaA yaSoduru","text_ar":"وَمَا يَصْدُرُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawoluhu Eano hawFY","text_ar":"قَوْلُهُ عَنْ هَوًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nor does his speech proceed from desire of self-gratification;"},{"kind":"text","text":"so the phrase may be well rendered,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nor does he speak from the desire"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (Mughnee.) One says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajaAbuwA Eano bawaA='K waAHidK","text_ar":"اَجَابُوا عَنْ بَوَا=ءٍ وَاحِدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bijawaAbK waAHidK","text_ar":"بِجَوَابٍ وَاحِدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They replied with one reply"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (T, S, O, K, all in art,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bwA^","text_ar":"بوا"},{"kind":"text","text":".) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAw^uwA","text_ar":"جَاوُوا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eano A=xirihimo","text_ar":"عَنْ ا=خِرِهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They came with the last of them;"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eano","text_ar":"عَنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being here syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bi","text_ar":"بِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they came all, without exception"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Axr","text_ar":"اخر"},{"kind":"text","text":".) [And in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qataluwhumo Eano A=xirihimo","text_ar":"قَتَلُوهُمْ عَنْ ا=خِرِهِمْ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They slew them with the last of them;"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they slew them all, without exception."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b10-  (9) It denotes the using a thing as an aid or instrument. (Mughnee, K.) Thus in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramayotu Eani Alqawosi","text_ar":"رَمَيْتُ عَنِ القَوْسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I shot with,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by means of, the bow"},{"kind":"text","text":"], accord. to Ibn-Málik; (Mughnee, K;) because one says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramayotu","text_ar":"رَمَيْتُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAlqawosi","text_ar":"بِالقَوْسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; both mentioned by Fr. (Mughnee.) [Another explanation of this phrase has been mentioned before.] ―         -b11-  (10) It is redundant, to compensate for another ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"En","text_ar":"عن"},{"kind":"text","text":"] suppressed (Mughnee, K.) Thus in the saying,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A^atajozaEu A_ino nafosN A^ataAhaA HimaAmuhaA\n                      \n                     \n                        fahal~aA A@l~atiY Eano bayoni janobayoka tadofaEu"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Art thou impatient if the decreed event of death befall a soul? but why wilt not thou repel from,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"defend, that which is between thy two sides?"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (Mughnee, K;) the meaning being,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tadofaEu Eani","text_ar":"تَدْفَعُ عَنِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@l~atiY bayona janobayoka","text_ar":"ا@لَّتِى بَيْنَ جَنْبَيْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (IJ, Mughnee;)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"En","text_ar":"عن"},{"kind":"text","text":"being suppressed before the conjunct noun ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AltY","text_ar":"التى"},{"kind":"text","text":"], and added after it. (Mughnee, K.) And sometimes it is redundant without compensation, when conjoined with a pronoun: AZ says that the Arabs make"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eanoka","text_ar":"عَنْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"redundant in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xu*o *aA Eanoka","text_ar":"خُذْ ذَا عَنْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Take thou,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"receive thou, this"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA:) [but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xu*o Eanoka","text_ar":"خُذْ عَنْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is expl. in the S and L, in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ax*","text_ar":"اخذ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xu*o maA A^aquwlu wadaEo Eanoka Al$~ak~a waAlmiraA='a","text_ar":"خُذْ مَا اَقُولُ وَدَعْ عَنْكَ الشَّكَّ وَالمِرَا=ءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 1 in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ax*","text_ar":"اخذ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aunofu*o Eanoka","text_ar":"اُنْفُذْ عَنْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", occurring in a trad., is expl. as meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daEohu","text_ar":"دَعْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Leave thou it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA:) or this means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"go thou from thy place; pass thou from it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nf*","text_ar":"نفذ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) [See also the last ex. in this paragraph.]       -A3-  The second manner of using it is, as a particle of the kind called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maSodariY~N","text_ar":"مَصْدَرِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [combining with an aor. following it to form an equivalent to an inf. n.,] as is done by the tribe of Temeem, (Mughnee, K, *) in what is termed their"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EanoEanap","text_ar":"عَنْعَنَة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K: [see R. Q. 1:]) they use it in the place of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ano","text_ar":"اَنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Mughnee;) saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEojabaniY Eano tafoEala","text_ar":"اَعْجَبَنِى عَنْ تَفْعَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mughnee, K,) for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ano tafoEala","text_ar":"اَنْ تَفْعَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thy doing"},{"kind":"text","text":"such a thing"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pleased me"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Mughnee.) Dhu-r-Rummeh says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A^aEano taras~amota mino xaroqaA='a manozilapF\n                      \n                     \n                        maA='u AlS~abaAbapi mino Eayonayoka masojuwmu"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Is thy having looked upon the traces of a place of"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2165},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abiding of"},{"kind":"text","text":"thy beloved"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Kharkà"},{"kind":"text","text":"the cause that"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the water of excessive love is shed from thine eyes?"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, Mughnee.) And thus they do in the case of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^an~a","text_ar":"اَنَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHam~adFA rasuwlu A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"مُحَمَّدًا رَسُولُ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$ohadu Ean~a","text_ar":"اَشْهَدُ عَنَّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I acknowledge,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"declare,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"testify, that Mohammad is the apostle of God"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Mughnee.)       -A4-  The third manner of using it is, as a noun, in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAnib","text_ar":"جَانِب"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mughnee, K, *) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAHiyap","text_ar":"نَاحِيَة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) and this is said to be in three cases. (Mughnee.) ―         -b2-  (1) It is when"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino","text_ar":"مِنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is prefixed to it; and this is of frequent occurrence: (Mughnee:) as in the saying,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"walaqado A^araAniY lilr~imaAHa dariyoy^apF\n                      \n                     \n                        mino Eano yamiyniY mar~apF waA^amaAmiY"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And verily I see me to be"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a ring for the spears to be aimed at, from the side of my right hand at one time, and from before me"},{"kind":"text","text":"at another time]: (Mughnee, K: *) and in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jiy^otu","text_ar":"جِيْتُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino Eano yamiynihi","text_ar":"مِنْ عَنْ يَمِينِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I came from the side of his right hand."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) In the opinion of Ibn-Málik,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino","text_ar":"مِنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"prefixed to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eano","text_ar":"عَنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is redundant; but accord. to others, it is used [as expl. above,] to denote the beginning of a space between two limits: these say that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaEadotu Eano yamiynihi","text_ar":"قَعَدْتُ عَنْ يَمِينِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY jaAnibi yamiynihi","text_ar":"فِى جَانِبِ يَمِينِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I sat in the side of his right hand"},{"kind":"text","text":"], either closely or otherwise; but if you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino","text_ar":"مِنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[before"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eano","text_ar":"عَنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], the sitting is particularized as being close to the first part of the lateral space. (Mughnee.) ―         -b3-  (2) It is also when"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY","text_ar":"عَلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is prefixed to it: (Mughnee:) thus in the saying,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"EalaY Eano yamiyniY mar~ati AlT~ayoru sun~aHaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"On,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"over, the side of my right hand, the birds passed along turning the right side towards me,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"turning the left side towards me;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the last word being a pl., accord. to analogy, of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAniHN","text_ar":"سَانِحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is used in two opposite senses]: (Mughnee, K:) but this usage is extraordinary; no other instance of it than that here cited having been preserved. (Mughnee.) ―         -b4-  (3) It is also when what is governed by it in the gen. case and the agent of the verb in connection with it are two pronouns having one application: so says Akh: as in the saying of Imra-el-Keys,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"daEo Eanoka nahobFA SiyHa fiY HajaraAtihi"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fadaEo Eanoka","text_ar":"فَدَعْ عَنْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see the entire verse cited and expl. in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hjr","text_ar":"حجر"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: but it is shown to be not a noun in such a case by this, that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAnib","text_ar":"جَانِب"},{"kind":"text","text":"may not take its place [unless used in a tropical sense]. (Mughnee. [See what has been said above, that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eanoka","text_ar":"عَنْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in a phrase of this kind is held to be redundant.])"}],"source_refs":["Msb","S","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n30650","headword_ar":"عَنٌّ","root":"En","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEonaAnN","text_ar":"اَعْنَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ah yaA^oxu*u fiY kul~i Ean~K","text_ar":"اـِنَّه يَاْخُذُ فِى كُلِّ عَنٍّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fY kl~ fan~K","text_ar":"فى كلّ فَنٍّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he enters upon every mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of speech or the like]; and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fY kl~ san~K","text_ar":"فى كلّ سَنٍّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n30840","headword_ar":"عَنٍ","root":"EnY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"is the part. n. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaniYa biAlA^amori","text_ar":"عَنِىَ بِالاَمْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuniYa","text_ar":"عُنِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]: (K, TA:) you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa biAlA^amori EanK","text_ar":"هُوَ بِالاَمْرِ عَنٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is disquieted"},{"kind":"text","text":"[&c.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by the affair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"case:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) [and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEoniY~N","text_ar":"مَعْنِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same, as part. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuniYa","text_ar":"عُنِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": or]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bihi","text_ar":"بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anaA maEoniY~N","text_ar":"اَنَا مَعْنِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EanaAniY ka*aA","text_ar":"عَنَانِى كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.], means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I am occupied"},{"kind":"text","text":"[either"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"actually"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in mind"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e., a thing that has occurred, or happened, to me; and sometimes one says, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anaA EaAnK","text_ar":"اَنَا عَانٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning the same, i. e., by the affair, or case, of another, from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eanayotu biA^amorihi","text_ar":"عَنَيْتُ بِاَمْرِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]: (Msb:) and one says [also],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biHaAjatika","text_ar":"بِحَاجَتِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anaA maEoniY~N","text_ar":"اَنَا مَعْنِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I am occupied by,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with, thy want"},{"kind":"text","text":"], from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euniytu biHaAjatika","text_ar":"عُنِيتُ بِحَاجَتِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) ―         -b2-  [And] part. n. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaniytu fiY AlA^amori","text_ar":"عَنِيتُ فِى الاَمْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]: you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anaA EanK","text_ar":"اَنَا عَنٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I am suffering difficulty, distress,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trouble;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fatigue,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"weariness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"in an affair, or case]: mentioned by Az. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","IAar","Msb"]}]}}